data.enText: the fact of including sb/sth; the fact of being included

data.chText: 他是否能被选入这个队还未定案。
data.enText: His inclusion in the team is in doubt.
a person or thing that is included

data.chText: 名单中包括一些意想不到的人。
data.enText: There were some surprising inclusions in the list.

tr: any small intracellular body found within another (characteristic of certain diseases)
example: an inclusion in the cytoplasm of the cell
he admired the inclusion of so many ideas in such a short work

value.def: Inclusion is the act of making a person or thing part of a group or collection.

example.ex: ...a confident performance which justified his inclusion in the team.
example.tran: 证明他入选该队当之无愧的自信表现

example.ex: ...the inclusion of the term 'couplehood' in a Dictionary of New Words.
example.tran: couplehood (夫妻之道)这一词条被收入《新词词典》

trans: 选择标准；纳入标准；纳入条件；入选标准；包含标准
